BFN 

<F P=106> [SDA report: "Defense Secretary Rifkind Visits Switzerland"] </F>
  [Text] On Thursday and Friday [2-3 June] British Defense 
Secretary Malcolm Rifkind discussed issues relating to security 
policy with Federal Councilor Kaspar Villiger. Rifkind 
explained that his country would welcome a Swiss blue helmet 
contingent and briefed Villiger on the missions of British blue 
helmets. Diplomatic efforts, peacekeeping operations, as well as 
humanitarian aid are extremely valuable measures that his 
country is implementing in armed conflicts all over the world. 
Villiger stated that after his conversation with Rifkind he 
sees his view again confirmed that, in particular, neutral 
states can provide important peacekeeping missions between the 
frontlines. 

